verses.text_plain: Praise waiteth for thee, O God, in Sion: and unto thee shall the vow be performed.
verses.verse_html:
1Praise waiteth for thee, O God, in Sion: and unto thee shall the vow be performed. ▼
▼ waiteth: Heb. is silent

tokens.text: and unto thee shall the vow

footnotes.body_html: ▼ waiteth: Heb. is silent

verses.text_plain: O thou that hearest prayer, unto thee shall all flesh come.
verses.verse_html: 2O thou that hearest prayer, unto thee shall all flesh come.

verses.text_plain: Iniquities prevail against me: as for our transgressions, thou shalt purge them away.
verses.verse_html:
3Iniquities prevail against me: as for our transgressions, thou shalt purge them away. ▼
▼ Iniquities: Heb. Words, or, Matters of iniquities

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Iniquities: Heb. Words, or, Matters of iniquities
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Iniquities: Heb. Words, or, Matters of iniquities

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the man whom thou choosest, and causest to approach unto thee, that he may dwell in thy courts: we shall be satisfied with the goodness of thy house, even of thy holy temple.
verses.verse_html: 4Blessed is the man whom thou choosest, and causest to approach unto thee, that he may dwell in thy courts: we shall be satisfied with the goodness of thy house, even of thy holy temple.

verses.text_plain: By terrible things in righteousness wilt thou answer us, O God of our salvation; who art the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that are afar off upon the sea:
verses.verse_html: 5By terrible things in righteousness wilt thou answer us, O God of our salvation; who art the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that are afar off upon the sea:

tokens.text: and of them that are afar off

verses.text_plain: Which by his strength setteth fast the mountains; being girded with power:
verses.verse_html: 6Which by his strength setteth fast the mountains; being girded with power:

verses.text_plain: Which stilleth the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.
verses.verse_html: 7Which stilleth the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.

verses.text_plain: They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at thy tokens: thou makest the outgoings of the morning and evening to rejoice.
verses.verse_html:
8They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at thy tokens: thou makest the outgoings of the morning and evening to rejoice. ▼
▼ rejoice: or, sing

verses.text_plain: Thou visitest the earth, and waterest it: thou greatly enrichest it with the river of God, which is full of water: thou preparest them corn, when thou hast so provided for it.
verses.verse_html:
9Thou visitest the earth, and waterest it: thou greatly enrichest it with the river of God, which is full of water: thou preparest them corn, when thou hast so provided for it. ▼
▼ and…: or, after thou hadst made it to desire rain

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and…: or, after thou hadst made it to desire rain
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and…: or, after thou hadst made it to desire rain

verses.text_plain: Thou waterest the ridges thereof abundantly: thou settlest the furrows thereof: thou makest it soft with showers: thou blessest the springing thereof.
verses.verse_html:
10Thou waterest the ridges thereof abundantly: thou settlest the furrows thereof: thou makest it soft with showers: thou blessest the springing thereof. ▼
▼ settlest: or, causest rain to descend into
 , ▼
▼ makest…: Heb. dissolvest it

footnotes.body_text: ▼ settlest: or, causest rain to descend into
footnotes.body_html: ▼ settlest: or, causest rain to descend into
▼ makest…: Heb. dissolvest it

verses.text_plain: Thou crownest the year with thy goodness; and thy paths drop fatness.
verses.verse_html:
11Thou crownest the year with thy goodness; and thy paths drop fatness. ▼
▼ with: Heb. of

verses.text_plain: They drop upon the pastures of the wilderness: and the little hills rejoice on every side.
verses.verse_html:
12They drop upon the pastures of the wilderness: and the little hills rejoice on every side. ▼
▼ rejoice…: Heb. are girded with joy

footnotes.body_text: ▼ rejoice…: Heb. are girded with joy
footnotes.body_html: ▼ rejoice…: Heb. are girded with joy

verses.text_plain: The pastures are clothed with flocks; the valleys also are covered over with corn; they shout for joy, they also sing.
verses.verse_html: 13The pastures are clothed with flocks; the valleys also are covered over with corn; they shout for joy, they also sing.
